226
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:29,000
Why are your brothers not here?

227
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,500
<i> It's your birthday.</i>

228
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:31,700
<i> I don't know.</i>

229
00:15:31,933 --> 00:15:34,900
<i>I haven't seen them
for two years.</i>

230
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:36,833
[MEN SHOUTING]

231
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:37,967
<i> What's that?</i>

232
00:15:37,967 --> 00:15:40,133
<i> Let's see what it is! Come on!</i>

233
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:45,000
- [GRUNTS]
<i> - That's enough!</i>

234
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,400
<i> Federico!</i>

235
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:48,133
<i> Stop it.</i>

236
00:15:48,133 --> 00:15:49,767
<i> This is a problem between us.</i>

237
00:15:49,767 --> 00:15:52,000
<i> Don't drag Michael into it!</i>

238
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,133
<i> Why shouldn't I?</i>

239
00:15:54,133 --> 00:15:55,967
<i>You're both making a fool
out of me!</i>

240
00:15:57,500 --> 00:16:00,600
[MIKE]<i> Believe me! We didn't
</i> want it to happen either!

241
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,500
<i>- Believe me!
- No!</i>

242
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,700
<i> You fooled me!</i>

243
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,533
[FEDERICO] Since when?!
Answer me!

244
00:16:06,533 --> 00:16:08,100
- [MIKE GRUNTS]<i> Aah!
</i> - That's enough!

245
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,900
<i> Federico, stop it.</i>

246
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:11,833
<i> The kids will hear us.</i>

247
00:16:12,467 --> 00:16:14,767
<i>Come on, let's go.
I'm begging you.</i>

248
00:16:14,767 --> 00:16:15,867
<i> Let's leave.</i>

249
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:19,033
<i>I trusted you
more than a friend!</i>

250
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:25,667
[HUFFING]

251
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,167
<i> Federico, wait!</i>

252
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:31,967
<i> Jade, let's go!</i>

253
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:35,067
<i> Federico!</i>

254
00:16:36,033 --> 00:16:37,467
<i> Federico!</i>

255
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:47,533
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

256
00:16:53,600 --> 00:17:00,533
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:02,733
Has he arrived?

258
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:03,767
Is that him?

259
00:17:03,767 --> 00:17:05,700
- Oh.
- Kiko's here!

260
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:08,067
Oh. He's here. Kiko!

261
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:12,567
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
Monette! Raphie!

262
00:17:12,567 --> 00:17:13,533
[MONETTE] Come!

263
00:17:13,967 --> 00:17:14,833
[RAPHIE] Is that him?

264
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:17,133
- [MONETTE] Yes.
- [RAPHIE] Monette.

265
00:17:17,133 --> 00:17:18,900
Kiko!

266
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:21,933
Let me help you
with your things.

267
00:17:21,933 --> 00:17:23,033
- My gosh.
- [KIKO] How are you?

268
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:24,733
Long time no see!

269
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:26,067
It has been five years.

270
00:17:26,067 --> 00:17:28,967
I know. I'm glad you still
remember my brother.

271
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:30,167
He's all grown up now.

272
00:17:30,167 --> 00:17:31,967
We already know that.

273
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:34,533
Here's the boat
going to Solara Island.

274
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:37,733
Your father has
been waiting for you there.

275
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:41,567
How's it going at the hotel?

276
00:17:41,567 --> 00:17:43,733
Well, it's still the same.
It's still close.

277
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:45,133
It's still not operational.

278
00:17:45,133 --> 00:17:47,733
Since the fire,
it hasn't been reopened yet.

279
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:50,900
I'm sure it'll feel different
because there are no people.

280
00:17:50,933 --> 00:17:53,567
It's like it became
a haunted hotel.

281
00:17:53,567 --> 00:17:54,833
No, it didn't.

282
00:17:55,633 --> 00:17:57,633
- How's your trip?
- Sir, let's go!

283
00:17:59,033 --> 00:18:06,000
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:30,900
[MONETTE] We're here!

285
00:18:33,033 --> 00:18:34,667
[RAPHIE] This way.

286
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:44,833
[KIKO] Papa said we have
something important to discuss.

287
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:46,700
[RAPHIE] That's what he
told us, too.

288
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:48,367
He said his kids
are coming home.

289
00:18:48,367 --> 00:18:50,033
Do you have any idea
what it is?

290
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:51,700
[MONETTE EXHALES HEAVILY]

291
00:18:52,233 --> 00:18:54,133
He suddenly called us.

292
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,200
Even Raphie and I
were surprised.

293
00:18:56,233 --> 00:18:57,400
But we'd be more surprised

294
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:59,767
if you
and your brothers reunite.

295
00:18:59,767 --> 00:19:00,967
[KIKO] Have they arrived?

296
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,867
[RAPHIE] You're the first one
to arrive.

297
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:05,833
[SIGHS] Finally.

298
00:19:06,633 --> 00:19:07,967
[RAPHIE] Sir's over there.

299
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:15,233
Pa.

300
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:17,733
Son.

301
00:19:31,433 --> 00:19:32,900
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

302
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:35,167
It's been a while
since I got my hands on these.

303
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:39,133
Perfect timing
for your brothers' arrival.

304
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:42,667
Do you remember, Kiko?

305
00:19:42,667 --> 00:19:44,367
When you were kids,

306
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:47,367
we'd always hang out
during the summer.

307
00:19:49,033 --> 00:19:52,800
I think this is the last photo
of us together.

308
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,133
It's been a long time,
hasn't it?

309
00:19:57,300 --> 00:20:00,833
[MIKE GRUNTING]

310
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,133
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

311
00:20:07,167 --> 00:20:14,100
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

312
00:20:21,467 --> 00:20:22,667
[KIKO] Pa.

313
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,433
Why did you
ask us to come here?

314
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:27,367
What's the matter?

315
00:20:30,033 --> 00:20:31,167
You said...

316
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:33,367
you have something
important to tell us.

317
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,067
[SIGHS]

318
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:38,367
Let's wait
for your brothers first.

319
00:20:38,367 --> 00:20:45,333
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:57,467
Good morning, sir.

321
00:21:02,267 --> 00:21:04,033
[EMPLOYEE]
Sir, sales keep dropping.

322
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:06,400
Chinese suppliers
are undercutting us online.

323
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,000
Almost half the price.

324
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:10,200
Plus free shipping.

325
00:21:11,867 --> 00:21:14,067
Sir, instead of suffering
more loss,

326
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:17,067
- should we just...
- [MARTIN] Shut down?

327
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,133
Shut down?

328
00:21:21,867 --> 00:21:23,833
Since when did you
become a coward, James?

329
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:28,233
We don't compete on price.

330
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:32,433
We compete by making
our competition irrelevant.

331
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:33,767
We pivot.

332
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:36,267
We turn our bookstores
into coffee shops.

333
00:21:36,867 --> 00:21:39,767
We will be the new
hangout spot and creative hub.

334
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:43,800
A place where online shops
can't compete.

335
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:48,867
This company will not close

336
00:21:48,867 --> 00:21:51,033
as long as I'm the one
running it.

337
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:54,167
Is that clear?

338
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:55,233
[JAMES] Yes, sir.

339
00:21:55,900 --> 00:21:57,167
Get back to work.

340
00:21:57,167 --> 00:22:04,067
[SOFT TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

341
00:22:09,933 --> 00:22:12,167
[GIO WHISTLING]

342
00:22:13,467 --> 00:22:15,867
[PHONE BUZZING]

343
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,833
Psh.

344
00:22:28,067 --> 00:22:29,133
[GIO EXHALES DEEPLY]

345
00:22:29,133 --> 00:22:36,033
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:22:38,233 --> 00:22:39,867
Where's my money?

347
00:22:39,867 --> 00:22:41,367
I'm going to pay you, Bok.

348
00:22:41,367 --> 00:22:42,367
[SMACKS]

349
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:45,300
You want me to kill you,
don't you?

350
00:22:46,267 --> 00:22:47,433
[BOK] Hmm?!

351
00:22:47,433 --> 00:22:50,300
[GIO HUFFING]

352
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:51,467
If you kill me,

353
00:22:51,467 --> 00:22:53,400
you'll never get
your money back.

354
00:22:54,267 --> 00:22:57,033
I need my money, Gio.

355
00:22:57,467 --> 00:22:59,400
You wouldn't want
my patience to run out!

356
00:23:01,233 --> 00:23:02,333
Remember this.

357
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:04,867
If you still don't give me
my money back next time,

358
00:23:04,867 --> 00:23:06,200
I'll kill you!

359
00:23:07,133 --> 00:23:08,200
[GIO GRUNTS]

360
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:15,333
Thank you!
See you again next time!

361
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:19,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

362
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:24,667
[SIZZLING]

363
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:26,967
Oh, Is that pork belly?

364
00:23:26,967 --> 00:23:28,967
Didn't the Doctor tell you
to take it easy on the fat?

365
00:23:28,967 --> 00:23:30,600
Right, Grandma?

366
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:32,133
This is for you!

367
00:23:32,133 --> 00:23:34,567
What are you blabbering about?
Isn't this your favorite?

368
00:23:34,567 --> 00:23:36,700
Alright, let me eat now.

369
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:39,767
Hey, hey, hey!

370
00:23:39,767 --> 00:23:42,533
You think I don't see
the wound on your lip, huh?

371
00:23:42,533 --> 00:23:43,867
Hmmp!

372
00:23:43,867 --> 00:23:46,067
- Where?
- Mm-hmm.

373
00:23:46,067 --> 00:23:48,433
Who hit you this time?

374
00:23:48,433 --> 00:23:51,133
It's nothing, Grandma.
Don't worry about it.

375
00:23:51,133 --> 00:23:53,667
What would you do
without me, huh?

376
00:23:53,667 --> 00:23:56,567
Come on, Grandma,
I'll die before you.

377
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,633
[GLASS THUDS]

378
00:23:58,633 --> 00:24:02,833
I'm not kidding around. Want me
to hit you with a ladle?

379
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:04,967
Alright, alright,
let's just eat.

380
00:24:04,967 --> 00:24:08,000
- Ouch, it's hot!
- Be careful!

381
00:24:11,100 --> 00:24:13,000
This doesn't have any fat.

382
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:15,000
Oh my goodness!

383
00:24:16,433 --> 00:24:18,400
I know that look.

384
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,867
How much?

385
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:24,700
Elena and I went to the salon
last week, remember?

386
00:24:24,700 --> 00:24:27,000
- And then we went to--
- Grandma, just tell me.

387
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,833
Your dad messaged.

388
00:24:28,867 --> 00:24:30,467
He wants you
to go to the hotel.

389
00:24:30,467 --> 00:24:33,533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

390
00:24:33,533 --> 00:24:36,167
I don't want to be involved
with Papa anymore.

391
00:24:36,167 --> 00:24:39,100
Well, to be fair, you all
had different mothers...

392
00:24:40,667 --> 00:24:42,533
That's why it's hard to bond.

393
00:24:42,533 --> 00:24:45,667
Grandma, let's not talk
about that anymore.

394
00:24:45,667 --> 00:24:47,500
I won't go there anymore.
I'm fine.

395
00:24:51,767 --> 00:24:53,967
Rebranding?

396
00:24:53,967 --> 00:24:56,700
Coffee shops? Creative hubs?

397
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:59,667
- Based on my projections...
- [CARLOS] Projections?

398
00:24:59,667 --> 00:25:01,067
[CARLOS] You know what I see?

399
00:25:01,067 --> 00:25:04,033
I only see a graph
that's going down.

400
00:25:04,067 --> 00:25:07,767
And you want to borrow
a big amount of money...

401
00:25:07,767 --> 00:25:10,700
just to turn it into a very
expensive hangout spot?

402
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:11,800
[PHONE BUZZING]

403
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:14,833
- I'll make it successful, Dad.
- [CARLOS] Enough!

404
00:25:14,833 --> 00:25:18,167
You'll use my money, Martin.

405
00:25:18,167 --> 00:25:20,500
And I make the decisions.

406
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:23,933
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

407
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:26,100
"PAPA: WHEN WILL
YOU COME HOME, SON?"

408
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:33,033
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC
PLAYING, FADES]

409
00:25:33,667 --> 00:25:36,133
[MOMMYLA] I'm getting old.

410
00:25:36,167 --> 00:25:39,900
When your mom died,
all I thought about was

411
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:42,133
me being here
to take care of you.

412
00:25:43,100 --> 00:25:45,900
I forgot that
I'm actually getting old.

413
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:48,033
[MOMMYLA] You need to be
around someone.

414
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:49,633
They need you there.

415
00:25:49,633 --> 00:25:51,233
And now he needs me?

416
00:25:51,233 --> 00:25:53,133
Where was he when Mama died?

417
00:25:53,133 --> 00:25:56,567
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

418
00:25:56,567 --> 00:25:58,900
He wasn't a good father,
grandma, and we both know it.

419
00:26:00,533 --> 00:26:02,167
But still!

420
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:04,533
[SIGHS]

421
00:26:04,533 --> 00:26:10,933
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES, FADES]

422
00:26:14,067 --> 00:26:16,300
I wonder what your brothers
look like now...

423
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:18,600
Who do you think is the most
handsome among you three?

424
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:21,033
[SCOFFS] Why are you even
asking, it's obviously me.

425
00:26:22,233 --> 00:26:24,000
You're so full of yourself.

426
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:28,633
- Raphie?
- Hmm?

427
00:26:28,633 --> 00:26:32,000
Does Papa still drink all day?

428
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:33,167
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

429
00:26:33,167 --> 00:26:36,967
[RAPHIE] Hasn't your dad always
been a heavy drinker?

430
00:26:36,967 --> 00:26:39,767
It only got worse
when the hotel closed.

431
00:26:45,867 --> 00:26:48,233
But you know what,
we're also thinking

432
00:26:48,233 --> 00:26:51,300
that Sir Michael might just
sell the whole property.

433
00:26:51,300 --> 00:26:53,867
That could be the reason
why he called for you three.

434
00:26:54,867 --> 00:26:57,300
Yeah, my mom and I
think so too.

435
00:26:58,033 --> 00:27:00,633
If we had to split
our shares,

436
00:27:00,633 --> 00:27:02,700
then I should take mine.

437
00:27:03,833 --> 00:27:05,867
Splitting the money is easy,

438
00:27:05,867 --> 00:27:09,267
but where will your dad live
if he loses the hotel?

439
00:27:09,267 --> 00:27:11,200
- He could live in your place.
- [CHUCKLES]

440
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:13,133
Sure, he can sleep next
to Monette.

441
00:27:13,133 --> 00:27:14,833
- [LAUGHS]
- Right?

442
00:27:14,833 --> 00:27:21,800
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

443
00:27:29,967 --> 00:27:32,033
[CHESCA]<i> What's up, bro?
</i> Are you already rich?

444
00:27:32,033 --> 00:27:34,100
- [GRUNTS]
- [REFRIGERATOR CLOSES]

445
00:27:34,100 --> 00:27:36,033
Are you crazy? Of course not.

446
00:27:36,033 --> 00:27:39,700
Come on, bro. I thought
you'd hit the jackpot.

447
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:42,067
[KIKO]<i> How are all
</i> the vegetables?

448
00:27:42,067 --> 00:27:45,833
Do a good job there, you're the
only one helping Mama around.

449
00:27:45,833 --> 00:27:47,867
Bro, you don't need
to remind me.

450
00:27:47,867 --> 00:27:49,700
I got everything under control.

451
00:27:50,733 --> 00:27:52,267
Besides...

452
00:27:52,267 --> 00:27:54,700
you shouldn't be worrying
about the farm anymore.

453
00:27:54,700 --> 00:27:55,967
Come on, man...

454
00:27:55,967 --> 00:27:57,767
you're the heir now.

455
00:27:57,767 --> 00:27:59,367
You'll inherit
everything there!

456
00:27:59,367 --> 00:28:00,900
<i> Hello!</i>

457
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:02,767
Oh, shut up! [CHUCKLES]

458
00:28:02,767 --> 00:28:05,667
By the way, mom said...

459
00:28:05,667 --> 00:28:07,867
to give your dad a kiss
for her!

460
00:28:07,867 --> 00:28:11,200
Hey, he might believe that!

461
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:13,800
He might fall in love
with me again!

462
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:15,833
I sure hope so.

463
00:28:15,833 --> 00:28:17,367
What do you mean
you hope so?

464
00:28:17,367 --> 00:28:19,800
- Mom likes the idea of it!
- [SCOFFS]

465
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:22,200
I was just joking, ma.

466
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,733
Just go with my dad.

467
00:28:23,767 --> 00:28:25,400
You might have another chance.

468
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:28,233
[CHUCKLES] Well, alright now!

469
00:28:28,233 --> 00:28:30,167
I'm going to sleep.

470
00:28:30,167 --> 00:28:32,100
Give mom a kiss for me, okay?

471
00:28:32,100 --> 00:28:34,033
<i> Sleep?</i>

472
00:28:34,033 --> 00:28:36,767
Are you sure you
can sleep there, bro?

473
00:28:36,767 --> 00:28:39,800
[SNEERS] You haven't been
there for a long time.

474
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:41,033
<i> And...</i>

475
00:28:41,033 --> 00:28:42,733
I heard that place closed down,

476
00:28:42,733 --> 00:28:45,400
<i>and no one stayed there
for so long.</i>

477
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:48,400
You never know, you might have
some unseen visitors there.

478
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:50,300
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

479
00:28:50,300 --> 00:28:53,067
You talk a lot,
I'm hanging up, bye.

480
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:55,400
[CHUCKLES]

481
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:57,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

482
00:28:57,900 --> 00:29:00,933
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

483
00:29:00,933 --> 00:29:02,233
What's that?

484
00:29:04,767 --> 00:29:09,433
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

485
00:29:09,433 --> 00:29:16,367
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

486
00:29:20,467 --> 00:29:22,000
Who's there?

487
00:29:24,767 --> 00:29:26,067
Kiko.

488
00:29:27,333 --> 00:29:28,933
Uncle Federico.

489
00:29:30,267 --> 00:29:32,100
[FEDERICO CHUCKLES]

490
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:33,967
Good evening, Uncle.

491
00:29:34,967 --> 00:29:36,367
Good evening.

492
00:29:36,367 --> 00:29:38,867
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

493
00:29:38,867 --> 00:29:40,967
[MIKE] Go back
to your room, Kiko.

494
00:29:40,967 --> 00:29:42,933
Your uncle and I need
to talk about something.

495
00:29:42,933 --> 00:29:50,433
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

496
00:29:53,733 --> 00:29:56,267
I see your youngest
is already home.

497
00:29:56,267 --> 00:29:59,167
Yes. I'm just waiting
for the other two.

498
00:29:59,167 --> 00:30:06,100
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

499
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,733
It's been months...

500
00:30:12,767 --> 00:30:14,367
but no one's given birth yet.

501
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:19,133
Sandro is gone.

502
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:22,767
We already buried the bastard.

503
00:30:22,767 --> 00:30:28,200
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

504
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:30,133
[SIGHS]

505
00:30:30,133 --> 00:30:32,933
We're safe.

506
00:30:32,933 --> 00:30:35,867
Our whole family is safe.

507
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:39,133
We can finally carry out
the plans we've had.

508
00:30:39,133 --> 00:30:46,067
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

509
00:30:48,433 --> 00:30:51,000
We no longer have any rivals
for the hidden treasure

510
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,400
in this hotel.

511
00:30:57,300 --> 00:30:59,367
There's no turning
back now, Federico.

512
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:05,567
We already got what we wanted.

513
00:31:05,567 --> 00:31:11,300
[FOREBODING MUSIC
CONTINUES, FADES]

514
00:31:15,033 --> 00:31:21,867
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

515
00:31:25,867 --> 00:31:28,833
[CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

516
00:31:36,933 --> 00:31:39,033
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

517
00:31:39,033 --> 00:31:40,733
Dad! Dad!

518
00:31:40,967 --> 00:31:43,000
Thank you so much, Dad.

519
00:31:43,233 --> 00:31:45,033
You made so many kids happy.

520
00:31:45,233 --> 00:31:47,833
Thank you, Dad, for sponsoring
their painting sessions, huh?

521
00:31:47,833 --> 00:31:50,800
- I'm so happy!
- That's good to hear.

522
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,700
You know, anything
for you, my princess.

523
00:31:53,233 --> 00:31:54,733
Let me know if
you need anything.

524
00:31:54,733 --> 00:31:56,733
Thank you, Dad.
You are the best dad

525
00:31:56,733 --> 00:31:58,967
in the world. [SMOOCHES]

526
00:31:58,967 --> 00:32:00,333
- Love you.
- I love you.

527
00:32:02,700 --> 00:32:05,067
Jade, sit down.

528
00:32:05,067 --> 00:32:10,300
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

529
00:32:10,300 --> 00:32:11,667
Leon.

530
00:32:13,733 --> 00:32:14,733
Dad.

531
00:32:14,733 --> 00:32:16,633
Wow! That smells good.

532
00:32:16,667 --> 00:32:17,900
Try this.

533
00:32:19,033 --> 00:32:20,900
- New specialty, Luna?
- Yes.

534
00:32:21,333 --> 00:32:22,667
Oh.

535
00:32:24,833 --> 00:32:25,900
Mm!

536
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:27,967
It's really good, dear.

537
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:30,000
Thanks, Dad.

538
00:32:30,700 --> 00:32:33,067
Dad, you said you have
something to tell us.

539
00:32:35,167 --> 00:32:36,233
Well...

540
00:32:37,967 --> 00:32:40,933
I just wanted
to tell you that, uh...

541
00:32:42,067 --> 00:32:43,633
Michael and I...

542
00:32:44,733 --> 00:32:46,200
We've reached an agreement.

543
00:32:49,367 --> 00:32:50,333
Really?

544
00:32:54,333 --> 00:32:55,333
Yeah.

545
00:32:58,933 --> 00:32:59,967
But why?

546
00:33:00,767 --> 00:33:02,100
I mean...

547
00:33:02,433 --> 00:33:04,867
The last time we went
to the hotel was, like, what?

548
00:33:04,867 --> 00:33:06,233
More than 10 years ago?

549
00:33:07,733 --> 00:33:09,333
And now you're suddenly okay?

550
00:33:10,733 --> 00:33:12,233
[LEON] Whatever the reason is,

551
00:33:12,867 --> 00:33:14,267
what matters is

552
00:33:14,267 --> 00:33:15,867
they're on good terms now.

553
00:33:17,933 --> 00:33:19,033
Leon is right.

554
00:33:20,233 --> 00:33:21,667
That said,

555
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:25,200
we will be having
a get-together at Hotel 88.

556
00:33:26,133 --> 00:33:27,467
Just like the old times.

557
00:33:29,433 --> 00:33:31,933
Exciting!

558
00:33:31,933 --> 00:33:33,233
[CHUCKLING]

559
00:33:35,233 --> 00:33:36,367
It's good with me.

560
00:33:36,933 --> 00:33:38,033
When are we going?

561
00:33:38,033 --> 00:33:39,033
[SMOOCHES]

562
00:33:40,100 --> 00:33:41,333
Where were you?

563
00:33:43,100 --> 00:33:45,100
I haven't seen you in days.

564
00:33:45,867 --> 00:33:47,133
Justin...

565
00:33:47,867 --> 00:33:49,100
Take a shower first.

566
00:33:51,067 --> 00:33:52,033
Why?

567
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,033
Just go.

568
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:56,800
[SCOFFS]

569
00:33:57,033 --> 00:33:59,367
I shall return.
Ready for a party.

570
00:33:59,367 --> 00:34:06,300
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

571
00:34:09,167 --> 00:34:11,167
The world is healing,
don't you think?

572
00:34:11,167 --> 00:34:14,233
Sir Michael and
Sir Frederico are talking again.

573
00:34:14,233 --> 00:34:15,833
Right?

574
00:34:15,833 --> 00:34:18,800
After a decade of them
being on bad terms,

575
00:34:19,200 --> 00:34:20,800
What changed?
What happened?

576
00:34:21,267 --> 00:34:24,267
You know,
let's stop overthinking.

577
00:34:24,267 --> 00:34:27,267
Let's think of the menu
we'll have for Easter Sunday.

578
00:34:27,267 --> 00:34:30,067
Because, like before,
the Almazans will be here.

579
00:34:30,100 --> 00:34:31,967
- They're coming? Wait.
- Yes.

580
00:34:31,967 --> 00:34:33,900
- Where is it?
- What are you looking for?

581
00:34:33,900 --> 00:34:35,067
Oh, here it is.

582
00:34:35,433 --> 00:34:38,033
I need to bring out
the big cauldron.

583
00:34:38,033 --> 00:34:40,300
Cauldron? You're doing
too much.

584
00:34:41,033 --> 00:34:42,000
Oh, come on.

585
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,400
I'm just excited, Monnette.

586
00:34:44,167 --> 00:34:45,367
[MONETTE] You're so silly.

587
00:34:53,933 --> 00:34:55,467
Isn't this too sudden?

588
00:34:58,233 --> 00:34:59,267
What is?

589
00:35:04,533 --> 00:35:06,033
Everything.

590
00:35:07,833 --> 00:35:08,567
The...

591
00:35:13,167 --> 00:35:15,000
reconciliation...

592
00:35:17,233 --> 00:35:18,867
The announcement...

593
00:35:20,233 --> 00:35:21,867
What needs to be announced?

594
00:35:26,867 --> 00:35:28,800
Is there a problem if...

595
00:35:30,333 --> 00:35:32,467
Michael and I are reconciling?

596
00:35:34,167 --> 00:35:35,200
If that's true...

597
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:37,167
then no.

598
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:43,100
You know, more than anything...

599
00:35:45,267 --> 00:35:46,400
that it's what I want.

600
00:35:48,567 --> 00:35:51,100
I'm doing this for my kids.

601
00:35:54,167 --> 00:35:55,500
That's what's important.

602
00:35:56,933 --> 00:35:57,933
So...

603
00:35:59,933 --> 00:36:01,200
What's the announcement?

604
00:36:08,467 --> 00:36:10,133
Just wait for a few days.

605
00:36:10,167 --> 00:36:13,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

606
00:36:25,300 --> 00:36:26,733
[OBJECT RUSTLES]

607
00:36:30,067 --> 00:36:31,233
W-Who's there?

608
00:36:33,500 --> 00:36:35,267
Monette? Raphie?

609
00:36:35,267 --> 00:36:41,600
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

610
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:42,600
Monette?

611
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:00,100
- Aah!
- Aah!

612
00:37:00,100 --> 00:37:02,067
Wait! Wait! Wait, sir!

613
00:37:02,067 --> 00:37:03,433
It's me, Raphie!

614
00:37:04,600 --> 00:37:06,233
[EXHALES SHARPLY]
My gosh, Raphie!

615
00:37:07,367 --> 00:37:09,100
What are you doing there?

616
00:37:09,100 --> 00:37:11,000
I'm taking out the trash.

617
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:13,767
Why are you wearing a mask
while taking out the trash?

618
00:37:13,767 --> 00:37:16,300
Why? Am I not allowed
to take care of my skin?

619
00:37:16,333 --> 00:37:17,767
My gosh, sir.

620
00:37:17,767 --> 00:37:20,467
Also, you shouldn't be out.

621
00:37:20,467 --> 00:37:21,800
It's Good Friday.

622
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:23,267
God is dead.

623
00:37:23,267 --> 00:37:25,100
It's not good to be out
late at night

624
00:37:25,100 --> 00:37:26,533
so let's go.

625
00:37:26,533 --> 00:37:29,133
- My gosh.
- I thought there was a thief.

626
00:37:30,700 --> 00:37:32,767
Let's go, sir.
It's not safe out here.

627
00:37:33,500 --> 00:37:35,100
Sir Kiko.

628
00:37:40,833 --> 00:37:42,667
[RUSTLING]

629
00:37:45,167 --> 00:37:46,500
<i> Papa's still the same.</i>

630
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:48,333
<i>He'll welcome us
in his drunken state.</i>

631
00:37:48,333 --> 00:37:50,267
<i>I'm here because he's going
to tell us something important.</i>

632
00:37:50,300 --> 00:37:51,567
<i>It's probably
bout money, right?</i>

633
00:37:51,567 --> 00:37:52,800
<i>- Get it out! Get it out!
- [CHOKES]</i>

634
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:53,833
<i> - Hey!
</i>- [KIKO COUGHS]

635
00:37:53,833 --> 00:37:56,200
<i> Jade? I'm Kiko from Hotel 88.</i>

636
00:37:56,200 --> 00:37:57,633
<i> The Almazans are here.</i>

637
00:37:57,633 --> 00:37:59,867
<i>It's nice to see
the three of you again.</i>

638
00:37:59,867 --> 00:38:01,000
<i> Just like before.</i>

639
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:02,633
<i>Aren't you going
to call your father?</i>

640
00:38:02,633 --> 00:38:04,200
<i> Reconciliation...</i>

641
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:06,800
<i>Is there a problem if
Michael and I reconcile?</i>

642
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,300
<i> What happened?</i>

